Electron Download/Set up on Linux (4/4/25)

1. Download Nodejs/npm
	# Download and install nvm:
	curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.40.2/install.sh | bash
	# in lieu of restarting the shell
	\. "$HOME/.nvm/nvm.sh"
	# Download and install Node.js:
	nvm install 22
	# Verify the Node.js version:
	node -v # Should print "v22.14.0".
	nvm current # Should print "v22.14.0".
	# Verify npm version:
	npm -v # Should print "10.9.2".
	
2. Download Electron 
	npm install --save-dev electron@latest
	#Test/verify
	#npx electron --v

3. Create and go to file
	file name should be name of project
	
4. Enter file
	npm init -y
5. Create a main.js or index.js file as well as index.html

6. Update package.json
	"main": "main.js" -- this could be main or index.js, depends on what you use
	"scripts": {
  		"start": "electron ."
	}
	
7. Start
	. electron


8. Desktop shortcut
	-ensure that the directory exists
	mkdir -p ~/.local/share/applications/
	-create file
	nano ~/.local/share/applications/UR10-Welder.desktop

	-it'll open an editor and need to input this information
	

Different options: 
	- exec is the response to which electron then added with the file path to the frontend
[Desktop Entry]
Version=1.0
Name=UR_10 Welder
Comment=This is the UR10 welder front end desktop application
Exec=/home/user1/.nvm/versions/node/v22.14.0/bin/electron /home/user1/Documents/UR_10FrontEnd
Icon=/home/user1/Documents/UR_10FrontEnd/UR_10.png
Terminal=true
Type=Application
Categories=Utility;
	- exec is the response that runs start.sh file
	/home/user1/Documents/UR_10FrontEnd/start.sh
	-creates shell
	sh -c 'cd /home/user1/Documents/UR_10FrontEnd && npm start'
	
	
Or using path key explicitly
[Desktop Entry]
Version=1.0
Name=UR_10 Welder
Comment=This is the UR10 welder front end desktop application
Exec=/home/user1/.nvm/versions/node/v22.14.0/bin/electron .
Path=/home/user1/Documents/UR_10FrontEnd
Icon=/home/user1/Documents/UR_10FrontEnd/UR_10.png
Terminal=false
Type=Application
Categories=Utility;

	- Press ctrl o to save, enter, ctrl x to exit 
	- Verify the file exists
	ls -la ~/.local/share/applications/UR10-Welder.desktop
	- Make it exicutable
	chmod +x ~/.local/share/applications/UR10-Welder.desktop
	- Add to Desktop
	cp ~/.local/share/applications/UR10-Welder.desktop ~/Desktop/
	
	- Make sure its properly formatted
	chmod +x ~/.local/share/applications/UR10-Welder.desktop
	chmod +x ~/Desktop/UR10-Welder.desktop
	- Try using launcher
	gtk-launch ur10-welder
	- Update desktop database
	update-desktop-database ~/.local/share/applications
	- Validate desktop file
	desktop-file-validate ~/.local/share/applications/UR10-Welder.desktop
	

	
